jurisdiction.title: American Association for the Advancement of Science

BB902B00DFE301312B9668A86D17958E.description: Ask "How do you know?" in appropriate situations and attempt reasonable answers when others ask the same question.

BB8F75E0DFE301312B9468A86D17958E.description: Interpret oral descriptions of real-world objects and events.

BB8F2280DFE301312B9368A86D17958E.description: Interpret pictures, drawings, and videos of real-world objects and events.

BB8EC330DFE301312B9268A86D17958E.description: Draw pictures that portray some features of the thing being described.

BB8E6D30DFE301312B9168A86D17958E.description: Describe and compare real-world objects in terms of number, shape, texture, size, weight, color, and motion.

BB8D6300DFE301312B8E68A86D17958E.description: Measure the length in whole units of objects using rulers and tape measures.

BB8D0650DFE301312B8D68A86D17958E.description: Make something out of paper, cardboard, cloth, wood, plastic, metal, or existing objects that can actually be used to perform a task.

BB8CB5B0DFE301312B8C68A86D17958E.description: Assemble, take apart, and reassemble constructions using interlocking blocks or other interconnecting pieces.

BB8C66C0DFE301312B8B68A86D17958E.description: Use hammers, screwdrivers, clamps, and scissors to shape materials and fasten them together.

BB8BBEE0DFE301312B8968A86D17958E.description: Make quantitative estimates of time intervals and the lengths and weights of familiar objects.

BB8B5E30DFE301312B8868A86D17958E.description: Explain to other students how they go about solving numerical problems.

BB8AEDA0DFE301312B8768A86D17958E.description: Give the sums and differences of single-digit numbers.

BB8A9F00DFE301312B8668A86D17958E.description: Use whole numbers in ordering, counting, identifying, measuring, and describing objects and events.

BB8A06B0DFE301312B8468A86D17958E.description: Raise questions about the world and be willing to seek answers to these questions by making careful observations and trying things out.

BB890440DFE301312B8168A86D17958E.description: Things in nature and things people make have very different sizes, weights, ages, and speeds.

BB882A70DFE301312B7F68A86D17958E.description: Some things change so slowly or so quickly that the changes are hard to notice while they are taking place.

BB87DA80DFE301312B7E68A86D17958E.description: Small changes can sometimes be detected by comparing counts or measurements at different times.

BB878400DFE301312B7D68A86D17958E.description: An object can change in various ways, such as in size, weight, color, or temperature.

BB872AD0DFE301312B7C68A86D17958E.description: People can keep track of some things, seeing where they come from and where they go.

BB86D870DFE301312B7B68A86D17958E.description: Objects change in some ways and stay the same in some ways.

BB861FB0DFE301312B7968A86D17958E.description: One way to describe something is to say how it is and isn't like something else.

BB85B7B0DFE301312B7868A86D17958E.description: A model of something is different from the real thing but can be used to learn something about the real thing.

BB855EA0DFE301312B7768A86D17958E.description: Many toys are like real things in some ways but not others. They may not be the same size, are missing many details, or are not able to do all of the same things.

BB84C070DFE301312B7568A86D17958E.description: When parts are put together, they can do things that they couldn't do by themselves.

BB847210DFE301312B7468A86D17958E.description: Something may not work if some of its parts are missing.

BB842330DFE301312B7368A86D17958E.description: Most things are made of parts.

BBC38830DFE301312C2D68A86D17958E.description: Reasoning can be distorted by strong feelings.

BBC32120DFE301312C2C68A86D17958E.description: People are more likely to believe your ideas if you can give reasons for them.

BBC27820DFE301312C2A68A86D17958E.description: Often a person can find out about a group of things by studying just a few of them.

BBC21D20DFE301312C2968A86D17958E.description: Sometimes people aren't sure what will happen because they don't know everything that might be having an effect.

BBC1CAB0DFE301312C2868A86D17958E.description: Some events can be predicted well and some cannot.

BBC16980DFE301312C2768A86D17958E.description: Some things are more likely to happen than others.

BBC0D4E0DFE301312C2568A86D17958E.description: Circles, squares, triangles, spheres, cubes, cylinders and other shapes can be observed in things found in nature and in things that people build.

BBC03BD0DFE301312C2368A86D17958E.description: Sometimes changing one thing causes changes in something else. In some situations, changing the same thing in the same way has the same result.

BBBFE2E0DFE301312C2268A86D17958E.description: Similar patterns may show up in many places in nature and in the things people make.

BBBF3F60DFE301312C2068A86D17958E.description: A quantity is stated as a number and a label, such as 4 inches or 7 blocks.

BBBEEFC0DFE301312C1F68A86D17958E.description: The first digit of a two-digit number describes how many sets of 10 there are in the number.

BBBE9890DFE301312C1E68A86D17958E.description: An important kind of relationship between things is one thing being part of a whole.

BBBE3A70DFE301312C1D68A86D17958E.description: Simple graphs can help to tell about observations.

BBBDC0B0DFE301312C1C68A86D17958E.description: Sometimes in describing things there is a need to use numbers between whole numbers.

BBBD7360DFE301312C1B68A86D17958E.description: Numbers can be used to count things, place them in order, measure them, or name them.

BBBC78A0DFE301312C1868A86D17958E.description: Tools such as thermometers and X-ray machines are used to help figure out whether a person is healthy.

BBBC1C70DFE301312C1768A86D17958E.description: Medicines may help those who do become sick to recover.

BBBBCBB0DFE301312C1668A86D17958E.description: Vaccinations and other scientific treatments are used to protect people from getting certain diseases.

BBBB2E50DFE301312C1468A86D17958E.description: Letters and numbers can be used to put things in a useful order.

BBBAD830DFE301312C1368A86D17958E.description: There are different ways to store things so they can easily be found later.

BBBA2FD0DFE301312C1168A86D17958E.description: Early forms of recording messages used markings on materials such as wood or stone.

BBB9DE10DFE301312C1068A86D17958E.description: People have always tried to communicate with one another. Signed and spoken language was one of the first inventions.

BBB986F0DFE301312C0F68A86D17958E.description: Devices can be used to send and receive messages quickly and clearly.

BBB92600DFE301312C0E68A86D17958E.description: Information can be sent and received in many different ways. Some allow answering back and some do not. Each way has advantages and disadvantages.

BBB86D10DFE301312C0C68A86D17958E.description: People burn fuels such as wood, oil, coal, or natural gas, or use electricity, to cook their food and warm their houses.

BBB7D0C0DFE301312C0A68A86D17958E.description: Some objects can be used over again.

BBB77D30DFE301312C0968A86D17958E.description: Tools are used to help make things, and some things cannot be made at all without tools. Different tools have different uses.

BBB72530DFE301312C0868A86D17958E.description: Several steps are usually involved in making things.

BBB6CF70DFE301312C0768A86D17958E.description: Some kinds of materials are better than others for making any particular thing. Materials that are better in some ways, such as stronger or cheaper, may be worse in other ways, such as heavier or harder to cut.

BBB62370DFE301312C0568A86D17958E.description: Machines keep food fresh by packaging and cooling and move the food long distances from where it is grown to where people live.

BBB5CEA0DFE301312C0468A86D17958E.description: Machines improve what people get from crops by helping in planting and harvesting.

BBB573F0DFE301312C0368A86D17958E.description: A crop that is fine when harvested may spoil before it gets to consumers.

BBB525E0DFE301312C0268A86D17958E.description: Part of a crop may be lost to pests or spoilage.

BBB4D700DFE301312C0168A86D17958E.description: To grow well, plants need enough warmth, light, and water. Crops must be protected from weeds and pests.

BBB485C0DFE301312C0068A86D17958E.description: Most food comes from farms either directly as crops or as the animals that eat the crops.

BBB383C0DFE301312BFD68A86D17958E.description: Rules at home, at school, and in the community let people know how to behave and what to expect from others and so can reduce the number of disputes.

BBB33380DFE301312BFC68A86D17958E.description: Some ways of dealing with disagreements work better than others. People who are not involved in a dispute may be helpful in solving it.

BBB2E240DFE301312BFB68A86D17958E.description: Disagreements may occur between family members, friends, and others.

BBB23730DFE301312BF968A86D17958E.description: People often trade things they have for things that they want.

BBB1D3D0DFE301312BF868A86D17958E.description: Rules can help to make sure that everyone is treated fairly.

BBB11500DFE301312BF668A86D17958E.description: Choices have consequences, some more serious than others.

BBB0A7E0DFE301312BF568A86D17958E.description: Different people may make different choices for different reasons.

BBB05220DFE301312BF468A86D17958E.description: Getting something one wants may mean giving up something in return.

BBAFAEF0DFE301312BF268A86D17958E.description: Changes happen in everyone's life, sometimes suddenly, more often slowly. People cannot control some changes, but they can usually learn to cope with them.

BBAF1180DFE301312BF068A86D17958E.description: People are born into some groups, placed into some groups, and choose to join some groups.

BBAE64F0DFE301312BEE68A86D17958E.description: People often choose to dress, talk, and act like their friends. They also often choose to do certain things in their own way.

BBAE0B40DFE301312BED68A86D17958E.description: Different families or schools have different rules and patterns for behavior. Some behaviors are not accepted in most families or schools.

BBADBF20DFE301312BEC68A86D17958E.description: People are alike in many ways and different in many ways.

BBACCDE0DFE301312BE968A86D17958E.description: Talking to someone may help people understand their feelings or problems and what to do about them.

BBAC7250DFE301312BE868A86D17958E.description: People react to personal problems in different ways. Some ways are more likely to be helpful than others.

BBAC0250DFE301312BE768A86D17958E.description: People have many different feelingssadness, joy, anger, fear, etc.about events, themselves, and other people.

BBAB5900DFE301312BE568A86D17958E.description: Some diseases are caused by germs, some are not. Diseases caused by germs may be spread by people who have them. Washing one's hands with soap and water reduces the number of germs that can get into the body or that can be passed on to other people.

BBAAFFC0DFE301312BE468A86D17958E.description: Some things people take into their bodies from the environment can hurt them.

BBAA8040DFE301312BE368A86D17958E.description: Eating a variety of healthful foods and getting enough exercise and rest help people to stay healthy.

BBA9C8B0DFE301312BE168A86D17958E.description: People can learn from each other by telling and listening, showing and watching, and imitating what others do.

BBA97990DFE301312BE068A86D17958E.description: Some of the things people do, like playing soccer, reading, and writing, must be deliberately learned. Practicing helps people to improve. How well one learns sometimes depends on how one does it and how often and how hard one tries to learn.

BBA92AB0DFE301312BDF68A86D17958E.description: People use their senses to find out about their surroundings and themselves. Different senses give different information.

BBA88010DFE301312BDD68A86D17958E.description: The brain enables human beings to think and sends messages to other body parts to help them work properly.

BBA83230DFE301312BDC68A86D17958E.description: Senses can warn individuals about danger; muscles help them to fight, hide, or get out of danger.

BBA7E100DFE301312BDB68A86D17958E.description: The human body has parts that help it seek, find, and take in food when it feels hungereyes and a nose for detecting food, legs to get to it, arms to carry it away, and a mouth to eat it.

BBA725D0DFE301312BD968A86D17958E.description: A human baby grows inside its mother until its birth. Even after birth, a human baby is unable to care for itself, and its survival depends on the care it receives from adults.

BBA6AD30DFE301312BD868A86D17958E.description: All kinds of animals have offspring, usually with two parents involved.

BBA60E60DFE301312BD668A86D17958E.description: People tend to live in families and communities in which individuals have different roles.

BBA5BAF0DFE301312BD568A86D17958E.description: People need water, food, air, waste removal, and a particular range of temperatures in their environment, just as other animals do.

BBA55430DFE301312BD468A86D17958E.description: People have different external features, such as the size, shape, and color of hair, skin, and eyes, but they are more like one another than like other animals.

BBA46020DFE301312BD168A86D17958E.description: Some kinds of organisms that once lived on Earth have completely disappeared, although they were something like others that are alive today.

BBA41210DFE301312BD068A86D17958E.description: Different plants and animals have external features that help them thrive in different kinds of places.

BBA36880DFE301312BCE68A86D17958E.description: Many materials can be recycled and used again, sometimes in different forms.

BBA31850DFE301312BCD68A86D17958E.description: Plants and animals both need to take in water, and animals need to take in food. In addition, plants need light.

BBA26810DFE301312BCB68A86D17958E.description: Living things are found almost everywhere in the world. There are somewhat different kinds in different places.

BBA209D0DFE301312BCA68A86D17958E.description: Animals eat plants or other animals for food and may also use plants (or even other animals) for shelter and nesting.

BBA15070DFE301312BC868A86D17958E.description: Most living things need water, food, and air.

BBA104A0DFE301312BC768A86D17958E.description: Magnifiers help people see things they could not see without them.

BBA069E0DFE301312BC568A86D17958E.description: Offspring are very much, but not exactly, like their parents and like one another.

BBA01310DFE301312BC468A86D17958E.description: There is variation among individuals of one kind within a population.

BB9F2C40DFE301312BC268A86D17958E.description: Some animals and plants are alike in the way they look and in the things they do, and others are very different from one another.

BB9E4070DFE301312BBF68A86D17958E.description: Magnets can be used to make some things move without being touched.

BB9DE830DFE301312BBE68A86D17958E.description: Things near the earth fall to the ground unless something holds them up.

BB9CFFB0DFE301312BBB68A86D17958E.description: The way to change how something is moving is to give it a push or a pull.

BB9CAC10DFE301312BBA68A86D17958E.description: Things move in many different ways, such as straight, zigzag, round and round, back and forth, and fast and slow.

BB9BFB70DFE301312BB868A86D17958E.description: The sun warms the land, air, and water.

BB9B5770DFE301312BB668A86D17958E.description: Things can be done to materials to change some of their properties, but not all materials respond the same way to what is done to them.

BB9B0720DFE301312BB568A86D17958E.description: Objects can be described in terms of their properties. Some properties, such as hardness and flexibility, depend upon what material the object is made of, and some properties, such as size and shape, do not.

BB9A4F00DFE301312BB368A86D17958E.description: Animals and plants sometimes cause changes in their surroundings.

BB99C3C0DFE301312BB268A86D17958E.description: Change is something that happens to many things.

BB9941D0DFE301312BB168A86D17958E.description: Chunks of rocks come in many sizes and shapes, from boulders to grains of sand and even smaller.

BB98A0F0DFE301312BAF68A86D17958E.description: Water left in an open container disappears, but water in a closed container does not disappear.

BB984AB0DFE301312BAE68A86D17958E.description: Water can be a liquid or a solid and can go back and forth from one form to the other. If water is turned into ice and then the ice is allowed to melt, the amount of water is the same as it was before freezing.

BB97F000DFE301312BAD68A86D17958E.description: The temperature and amount of rain (or snow) tend to be high, low, or medium in the same months every year.

BB974BC0DFE301312BAB68A86D17958E.description: The moon looks a little different every day but looks the same again about every four weeks.

BB96F990DFE301312BAA68A86D17958E.description: The sun can be seen only in the daytime, but the moon can be seen sometimes at night and sometimes during the day. The sun, moon, and stars all appear to move slowly across the sky.

BB96A150DFE301312BA968A86D17958E.description: There are more stars in the sky than anyone can easily count, but they are not scattered evenly, and they are not all the same in brightness or color.

BB958910DFE301312BA668A86D17958E.description: When a group of people wants to build something or try something new, they should try to figure out ahead of time how it might affect other people.

BB9529A0DFE301312BA568A86D17958E.description: People, alone or in groups, are always inventing new ways to solve problems and get work done. The tools and ways of doing things that people have invented affect all aspects of life.

BB947EE0DFE301312BA368A86D17958E.description: People may not be able to actually make or do everything that they can design.

BB93DCA0DFE301312BA168A86D17958E.description: When trying to build something or to get something to work better, it usually helps to follow directions if there are any or to ask someone who has done it before for suggestions.

BB938A00DFE301312BA068A86D17958E.description: Tools are used to do things better or more easily and to do some things that could not otherwise be done at all. In technology, tools are used to observe, measure, and make things.

BB928C10DFE301312B9D68A86D17958E.description: Numbers and shapes can be used to tell about things.

BB91E940DFE301312B9B68A86D17958E.description: Things move, or can be made to move, along straight, curved, circular, back-and-forth, and jagged paths.

BB9199F0DFE301312B9A68A86D17958E.description: Patterns can be made by putting different shapes together or taking them apart. Patterns may show up in nature and in the things people make.

BB914620DFE301312B9968A86D17958E.description: Circles, squares, triangles, and other shapes can be found in nature and in things that people build.

BB828D80DFE301312B6F68A86D17958E.description: A lot can be learned about plants and animals by observing them closely, but care must be taken to know the needs of living things and how to provide for them in the classroom.

BB823C00DFE301312B6E68A86D17958E.description: In doing science, it is often helpful to work with a team and to share findings with others. All team members should reach their own individual conclusions, however, about what the findings mean.

BB81E3A0DFE301312B6D68A86D17958E.description: Everybody can do science and invent things and ideas.

BB812F10DFE301312B6B68A86D17958E.description: When people give different descriptions of the same thing, it is usually a good idea to make some fresh observations instead of just arguing about who is right.

BB80CD70DFE301312B6A68A86D17958E.description: Describing things as accurately as possible is important in science because it enables people to compare their observations with those of others.

BB8068F0DFE301312B6968A86D17958E.description: Tools such as thermometers, magnifiers, rulers, or balances often give more information about things than can be obtained by just observing things unaided.

BB801060DFE301312B6868A86D17958E.description: People can often learn about things around them by just observing those things carefully, but sometimes they can learn more by doing something to the things and noting what happens.

BB7F5F90DFE301312B6668A86D17958E.description: When a science investigation is done again in a different place, we expect to get a very similar result.

BB7F0EB0DFE301312B6568A86D17958E.description: When a science investigation is done the way it was done before, we expect to get a very similar result.
